name: CoreAPI Security_Role
about:
Description

The CoreAPI Security_Role API enables to access roles that are defined in the Roles tool.

With this API, you can list all existing roles within the system, fetch all information regarding a specific role, delete a role and, create roles.

Prerequisites: In order for the API to work, you will have to change the endpoint in the General tab.

Operations  performed

Important note: Please review the definitions and the request/response bodies for each operation. In certain definitions, you will a description next each field. If not, view the example data in the selected operation.

/List

Get the list of available roles. Within each object in the returned array, the UUID of each item is placed. This is the same value that /Get operation requires.

In the example data, you will find the response body of this operation.

Body
Definition
Request
None
Response
List

/Get

Get the details for a specific role.

In the example data, you will find the response body of this operation.

Body
Definition
Request
ID
Response
Get

/Delete

Delete a specific role.

Body
Definition
Request
ID
Response
Status

/Save

Create a role.

In the example data, you will find the request body of this operation.

Important note:

In the create definition, you must include all available ACL roles thus, all fields besides description and package which are optional. Inside the /Save operation, you'll find an example payload for the request body. You'll use this, adjusting the mode field to fit your needs. The mode field accepts values N, E, and D, corresponding to None, Edit, and Display, respectively. You can find these values in the Role tool. It's important to note that ACL roles are grouped into parent ACLs, which have tight correlations and operate independently at the parent-child level. Therefore, please review the mode dependencies between parent and child ACLs in the Role tool before creating your request body.

Body
Definition
Request
CreateReq
Response
CreateResp

If you wish to edit an existing role, then you can provide in the request body the CreateResp by providing the UUID of the role you want to edit and the correct ACL structure.
